osterman <- sjlabelled::read_stata("https://cgmoreh.github.io/HSS8005-data/osterman.dta")

ggplot(osterman, aes(y = trustindex3, x = eduyrs25)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 0.03) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") + 
  scale_y_continuous(n.breaks = 15) + 
  scale_x_continuous(n.breaks = 10)

Three linear models

lm_data <- osterman |> select(trustindex3, eduyrs25, agea, female) |> 
  mutate(med_trust = trustindex3 - median(trustindex3)) |> 
  mutate(d_trust = trustindex3 >= median(trustindex3))

Three linear models

  mutate(med_trust = trustindex3 - median(trustindex3)) |> 
  mutate(d_trust = trustindex3 >= median(trustindex3))

lm1 <- lm(trustindex3 ~ eduyrs25 + agea + female, lm_data)
lm2 <- lm(med_trust ~ eduyrs25 + agea + female, lm_data)
lm3 <- lm(d_trust ~ eduyrs25 + agea + female, lm_data)

lm_data <- osterman |> select(trustindex3, eduyrs25, agea, female) |> 
  mutate(med_trust = trustindex3 - median(trustindex3)) |> 
  mutate(d_trust = trustindex3 >= median(trustindex3))

lm_table <- modelsummary::modelsummary(list(
                                "lm" = lm1, 
                                "lm_cent" = lm2, 
                                "lm_prob" = lm3), 
                                statistic = 'conf.int')

The logit model

m_logit <- glm(d_trust ~ eduyrs25 + agea + female, family = binomial(link = "logit"), data = lm_data)
plot_predictions(m_logit, condition = c("eduyrs25"))

The probit model

m_probit <- glm(d_trust ~ eduyrs25 + agea + female, family = binomial(link = "probit"), data = lm_data)
plot_predictions(m_probit, condition = c("eduyrs25"))

Probabilities, Odds, Log-odds (logit), Odds Ratios


\(prob = \{0, \dots, 1\}\)


\(odds = {prob \over (1-prob)}\)


\(log\_odds = \ln(odds)\)


\(odds = {\rm e}^{\ln(odds)}\)


\(odds\_ratio = {odds1 \over odds2} = {{prob1 \over (1-prob1)} \over {prob2 \over (1-prob2)}}\)
